,Recommended,271360,17631935,"Posted: 20 August, 2015",all,Liam 🍋,"The game is very enjoyable, it has a good selection of production, sale and transport methods to begin with, a nice early game, the mid game introduces much more complicated production chains, which you can however ignore if you prefer simpler production chains. As of writing this review, I have not gotten to the late game yet.I would also not be too quick in comparing it with OpenTTD, as some reviewers seem to do. The similarities between the games are merely that they are 2D isometric games which feature vehicles. The base game of OpenTTD focuses on transporting one of about 10 different goods with very simple production chains, this game features complex production chains and much more flexible vehicles, which allow you a much greater ability to plan efficient routes (For example a truck can transport one good one way and another the other way)Overall I think you should try the game out. As other reviewers pointed out, there is the chance it might not run on your computer, however if that proves to be the case you can just take advantage of Steam's refund policy.In the past, the game had low frame rate issues, but I'm very happy to report that this has been fixed! The game runs very smoothly now!"
