,Recommended,271360,28006303,"Posted: 28 November, 2016",all,LeeEnfieldAS37,"Bought this game when it lanched as 'Industry Giant 2: Gold Edition' in 2003; It quickly became my favourite and the only game I would play on my new laptop at the time.7 years later I found I could no longer play it after installing it on a new Windows 7 PC due to a graphics driver updated from Nvidia that made it unplayable. I emailed JoWood support and recieved no response. I eventually concluded that JoWood were never going to put the effort into fixing a 7 year old game and then shortly after they disappeared into the history books.13 years after the release and I once again get to enjoy this classic game. The more I play it the more I realise how advanced it was for its time, features such as the control of production, influces of a city's growth, but it is all to do with supply and demand."
